article.headline: Centenary 69, UMKC 68
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Lance Hill scored with 2.2 seconds left to lift Centenary to a 69-68 victory over UMKC on Saturday night. Prior to Hill's late-game heroics, Alexander Starr led Centenary (9-17, 3-8 Mid-Con Conference) with 31 points and 10 rebounds. Starr was 12-of-20 shooting from the field, including three 3-pointers. Nick stallings scored 15 for Centenary, which led 36-24 at halftime, while Hill finished with 11 and Tyrone Hamilton 10. Dane Brumagin led UNKC (8-18, 3-7) with 31 points on 10-of-17 shooting, including four 3-pointers, while Quinton Day added 12 points.
